bug.short_desc: Ability to reopen a task when 'REOPENED' state is not available.

long_desc.thetext: Red Hat bugzilla workflow does not have 'REOPENED' state. Bugs can be closed, and the assigned again. Is there a way to tell mylyn to use 'ASSIGNED' instead of reopened, when 'Reopen' button is used?
Frank, do you know if is this is possible by specifying a custom workflow definition?

(In reply to comment #1) > Frank, do you know if is this is possible by specifying a custom workflow > definition?
Yes you can use a custom workflow but you must provide an Custom Workflow Description File or enable xmlrpc.

The wiki for the custom workflow does not list ReopenCustomStatus and ResolvedCustomStatus.

For readhat I found the problem that we get no response for the Products "Fendora" and "Fendora EPEL" when using the xmlrpc webservice.
So I implement a new option group for xmlrpc.
With this redhat can use workflow but not for default milestones (which use webservice Product.get) until we know why this fail.

Hey Frank,
Thank you so much for your work.
I was able to configure my Mylyn to work more or less properly with RH bugzilla.
I've rebuild mylyn with your patch, set custom transitions file and deselect default milestones in the repository configuration. Then after refresh things started working significantly better.
I will conclude more testing - it looks like your comments say that it is important to deselect default milestones checkbox, and things should work with xmlrpc, without the custom transitions file, am I reading this right?

(In reply to comment #12) > Hey Frank, > > Thank you so much for your work. > > I was able to configure my Mylyn to work more or less properly with RH > bugzilla. > > I've rebuild mylyn with your patch, set custom transitions file and deselect > default milestones in the repository configuration. Then after refresh > things started working significantly better.
The problem is that we actual load the configuration twice. The first time with config.cgi (file size > 42 MB) and then we try in one web service call to get the information for all defined products. After some test I found that even if we call the webservice for a single product we can not get the Values for the following two products ("Fedora", "Fedora EPEL"). I think we have here an Bugzilla problem if the result of an call gets to big!
> > I will conclude more testing - it looks like your comments say that it is > important to deselect default milestones checkbox, and things should work > with xmlrpc, without the custom transitions file, am I reading this right?
Yes with this we read the configuration once and use an other web service call for the transformations.
Maybe we should do some work and use only web services for the configuration. But then we need other reviews as a base for this https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/8752/ (372600: create new storage structure) and https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/9796/ (372592: support Disabling Old Components, Versions and Milestones of Bugzilla 4.2)
